This is a reflective time of year, and there=E2=80=99s a natural instinct=
=E2=80=94both editorially and biologically, frankly=E2=80=94to wrap a narra=
tive around the past 12 months and annotate it for the memory books. And wh=
ile
I could certainly indulge that sort of whimsy, I think the behavior slightl=
y misreads the moment. As I chewed over these D.C.-themed storylines at the=
 Riggs, I became increasingly alive to the observation that the next severa=
l quarters will be far more fascinating than the ones just traversed.

